article.headline: Stephen F.Austin 63, Texas-Tyler 47
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas (AP) -- Matt Kingsley scored 22 points to lift Stephen F. Austin past Texas-Tyler 63-47 in both teams' season opener Friday night. The Lumberjacks jumped out to a 38-27 halftime lead and extended their lead despite shooting just 33 percent in the second half. Patrick Branche scored 11 points for Texas-Tyler. Josh Alexander added 18 points for Stephen F. Austin. Stephen F. Austin shot just 39 percent from the floor, but the Lumberjacks forced the Patriots into 26 turnovers. Kingsley was 7-of-13 from the floor and 8-of-9 from the foul line.
